        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>Stack and PlanSwift are the two most commonly compared standalone takeoff platforms. Both handle the core job: measuring linear, area, and count quantities from PDF plan sets and producing estimate output. The differences come down to collaboration model, workflow depth, pricing structure, and whether you want a modern cloud platform or a flexible desktop tool.</p>

        <blockquote>
          <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> If you have a team of estimators working on commercial bids collaboratively, Stack's cloud-first architecture makes sense. If you estimate primarily solo or in a small shop, PlanSwift's deeper assembly system and perpetual license option offer better value.</p>
        </blockquote>

